Learning Objectives
At the end of this project, you are expected to be able to explain to anyone, without the help of Google:
What is the purpose and scope of an ISMS (Information Security Management System) based on ISO/IEC 27001 and 27002?
How can you analyze audit findings to identify non-conformities with ISO/IEC 27001 clauses?
Which specific ISO/IEC 27001 clauses apply to asset management, physical security, and backup procedures?
What corrective actions can be proposed to resolve non-conformities identified in an internal audit?
How can additional ISO/IEC 27002 controls strengthen an organization’s security and mitigate residual risks?
What practical examples demonstrate the effectiveness of ISO/IEC 27002 controls in reducing security vulnerabilities?
How do you write a structured, professional vulnerability assessment report that adheres to ISO standards and can be presented to management?
Why is continuous improvement important for maintaining and enhancing an ISMS, and how can it be achieved in practice?
What best practices should be followed when referencing ISO documentation and anonymizing sensitive information in security reports?
How do you ensure that a Google Docs report is properly shared and accessible as part of a project submission?

Requirements
General
Report-Based: Create a structured vulnerability assessment report aligned with ISO/IEC 27001 and 27002.
Documentation: Ensure the report is professional, comprehensive, and well-organized.
Legal and Ethical Considerations: Demonstrate awareness of relevant cybersecurity laws and ethical guidelines.
Compliance Awareness: Discuss applicable compliance frameworks like GDPR, HIPAA, or PCI-DSS.
ISO/IEC 27001 Clause Reference: Map non-conformities to specific ISO/IEC 27001 clauses.
Practical Recommendations: Propose actionable corrective measures and additional ISO/IEC 27002 controls.
Supporting Evidence: Provide evidence (screenshots, logs) while anonymizing sensitive data.
Clear Submission Instructions: Create and share the report in Google Docs, set sharing to "Anyone with the link can view."
Focus on Continuous Improvement: Emphasize the importance of regular audits and ongoing security improvements.
